  "chapter": {
    "number": 15,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Burden against Moab"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "This is the burden against Moab:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "Ar in Moab is ruined,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "destroyed in a night!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Kir in Moab is devastated,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "destroyed in a night!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Dibon goes up to its temple",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to weep at its high places.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Moab wails over Nebo,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as well as over Medeba.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "Every head is shaved,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "every beard is cut off.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In its streets they wear sackcloth;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "on the rooftops and in the public squares",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they all wail, falling down weeping.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heshbon and Elealeh cry out;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "their voices are heard as far as Jahaz.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Therefore the soldiers of Moab cry out;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "their souls tremble within.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My heart cries out over Moab;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "her fugitives flee as far as Zoar,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "as far as Eglath-shelishiyah.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2571
          },
          {
            "text": "With weeping they ascend the slope of Luhith;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they lament their destruction on the road to Horonaim.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The waters of Nimrim are dried up,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the grass is withered;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the vegetation is gone,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the greenery is no more.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So they carry their wealth and belongings",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "over the Brook of the Willows.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2572
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For their outcry echoes to the border of Moab.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Their wailing reaches Eglaim;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "it is heard in Beer-elim.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The waters of Dimon",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2573
          },
          {
            "text": "are full of blood,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but I will bring more upon Dimonâ€”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "a lion upon the fugitives of Moab",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and upon the remnant of the land.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 2571,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or Zoar, like a heifer three years of age.",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 15,
          "verse": 5
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 2572,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or Poplars",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 15,
          "verse": 7
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 2573,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "MT, twice in this verse; DSS and Vulgate Dibon; Dimon, a wordplay on Dibon (see verse 2), sounds like the Hebrew for blood.",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 15,
          "verse": 9
        }
      }
    ]
  },
